H.B. 617
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Mar 31, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH40342-MHfa-71A
Short Title: Supporting Small Farmers for NC's Future Act. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Jeffers.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO SUPPORT SMALL FARMERS IN NORTH CAROLINA BY PROVIDING
3 GRANT FUNDING TO ENSURE THE FUTURE VIABILITY OF NORTH CAROLINA'S
4 FAMILY FARMS AND BY LOWERING THE INCOME REQUIREMENT FOR
5 QUALIFYING FARMERS FOR PURPOSES OF THE SALES TAX EXEMPTION FOR
6 FARMERS.
7 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
8 SECTION 1. Findings and Purpose. – The General Assembly finds that decades of
9 barriers to entry, rising land prices, and economic consolidation has led to the loss of millions of
10 acres of land farmed by small farmers. The General Assembly further finds that financial
11 assistance through targeted grants can help address disparities and contribute to the long-term
12 success of small farmers. The purpose of this act is to support the viability and sustainability of
13 small farmers in North Carolina by providing financial assistance and tax relief to support these
14 farmers.
15 SECTION 2. Chapter 106 of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
16 Article to read:
17 "Article 61B.
18 "Small Farmers Support Grant Program.
19 "§ 106-748. Definitions.
20 The following definitions apply in this Article:
21 (1) Commissioner. – The Commissioner of Agriculture and Consumer Services.
22 (2) Department. – The North Carolina Department of Agriculture and Consumer
23 Services.
24 (3) Eligible individual. – A resident of this State who meets all of the following
25 criteria:
26 a. Is at least 21 years of age.
27 b. Is a small farmer.
28 c. Had an annual income from farming operations for the preceding
29 taxable year of at least one thousand dollars ($1,000) or more.
30 (4) Eligible purpose. – Any of the following:
31 a. Purchases of mechanized equipment for harvest and crop
32 management.
33 b. Farm infrastructure, including livestock fencing.
34 c. Food processing equipment.
*DRH40342-MHfa-71A*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (5) Small farmer. – A farmer with a gross cash farm income of three hundred
2 thousand dollars ($300,000) or less, as determined in a manner as the
3 Department may specify.
4 "§ 106-749. Small Farmers Support Grant Program established.
5 (a) Program Established. – The Small Farmers Support Grant Program (Program) is
6 established within the North Carolina Department of Agriculture to support current small farmers
7 and to encourage the continued financial viability of those farmers in the field of agriculture. The
8 Small Farmer Growth Fund (Fund) is established as a special revenue fund. The Fund shall
9 consist of gifts, grants, and donations from non-State entities and General Fund appropriations
10 for the support of the Program established by this Article. The Fund shall be used for the
11 provision of grants to eligible individuals for essential inputs, equipment, and operational
12 improvements to their farming operations.
13 (b) Grants. – Grants from the Fund are subject to the following procedures and
14 restrictions:
15 (1) An eligible individual seeking a grant shall submit an application on a form
16 and in a manner approved by the Commissioner that specifies one or more
17 eligible purposes for the requested grant funding.
18 (2) The Commissioner may establish priorities for grants among all eligible
19 individuals based on criteria that include farm size, income levels, and
20 economic hardship, including lack of access to capital and operational
21 support.
22 (3) The Commissioner may establish tiered maximum grant amounts based on
23 financial hardship, demonstrated need, and other criteria the Department feels
24 will maximize the ability of the Program to increase the long-term viability
25 and sustainability of small farmers.
26 (c) The Department shall establish an advisory committee to monitor the Program's
27 effectiveness and make recommendations for improvements.
28 (d) The Department shall adopt rules to carry out the provisions of this Article."
29 SECTION 3.(a) Funding. – The sum of twenty million dollars ($20,000,000) in
30 recurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year is appropriated from the General Fund to the
31 Department of Agriculture and Consumer Services for the Small Farmer Growth Fund to be
32 allocated as follows:
33 (1) Twelve million dollars ($12,000,000) to the Small Farmers Support Grant
34 Program (Program) established in G.S. 106-749, as enacted by Section 2 of
35 this act, for any eligible purpose of the Program.
36 (2) Three million dollars ($3,000,000) to the Program to be used for grants for
37 new or additional cold storage equipment for storage of fresh produce or meat.
38 (3) Four million dollars ($4,000,000) to provide a grant to the Carolina Farm
39 Steward Association for the FarmsSHARE program.
40 (4) One million dollars ($1,000,000) to the Program, to be used to provide bridge
41 loans to enable eligible farmers to participate in the Environmental Quality
42 Incentives Program under the Natural Resources Conservation Service of the
43 United States Department of Agriculture (NRCS EQIP). The Program will
44 loan the money on terms that coincide with the NRCS EQIP grant contract,
45 and loans must be paid directly back to the Program through an assignment of
46 payment from NRCS EQIP.
47 SECTION 3.(b) The Department may retain up to one percent (1%) of the funds
48 appropriated by this section for administrative costs related to the Program established by Article
49 61B of Chapter 106 of the General Statutes, as enacted by Section 2 of this act, and the other
50 programs funded in subsection (a) of this section. The Department may establish up to two FTE
51 positions in its Small Farmer Division to support these initiatives.
